107
00:06:05,670 --> 00:06:06,953
- The LEO?
- Mhmm.

108
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:10,994
- I've heard it's a pretty long list.

109
00:06:10,994 --> 00:06:12,000
- Well if it was such a long list

110
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:14,130
I wouldn't have asked
to get a look at you.

111
00:06:14,130 --> 00:06:15,370
You want the appointment?

112
00:06:15,370 --> 00:06:16,720
- Yes, very much.

113
00:06:16,720 --> 00:06:18,540
- [Dan] Then don't be coy about it.

114
00:06:18,540 --> 00:06:19,940
- No problem.

115
00:06:19,940 --> 00:06:21,380
Who's my competition?

116
00:06:21,380 --> 00:06:22,380
- Not for me to say.

117
00:06:23,350 --> 00:06:24,670
The best advice I can offer you

118
00:06:24,670 --> 00:06:26,500
is don't be faint-hearted when it comes

119
00:06:26,500 --> 00:06:28,900
to acting in your own self-interest.

120
00:06:28,900 --> 00:06:30,770
The LEO Board makes policy.

121
00:06:30,770 --> 00:06:32,630
That's not a bad way to introduce yourself

122
00:06:32,630 --> 00:06:33,603
to public life.

123
00:06:34,829 --> 00:06:35,662
Well.

124
00:06:37,440 --> 00:06:38,553
