154
00:08:11,455 --> 00:08:12,433
- (chuckling) Yeah.

155
00:08:13,920 --> 00:08:14,753
Well.

156
00:08:17,700 --> 00:08:20,913
Mary Beth, I'm up for the LEO Board.

157
00:08:22,110 --> 00:08:24,530
I mean I'm way high up on the list.

158
00:08:24,530 --> 00:08:25,940
- When did you hear that?

159
00:08:25,940 --> 00:08:27,830
- I met with Daniel Broadbent.

160
00:08:27,830 --> 00:08:29,020
- I know that name.

161
00:08:29,020 --> 00:08:30,810
- Course you know that name.

162
00:08:30,810 --> 00:08:31,698
He's the one-

163
00:08:31,698 --> 00:08:32,531
(phone ringing)

164
00:08:32,531 --> 00:08:33,510
- That's Douglas Trayne.

165
00:08:33,510 --> 00:08:34,920
He's been asking about you all afternoon.

166
00:08:34,920 --> 00:08:37,700
I promised I'd buzz as
soon as you got back.

167
00:08:37,700 --> 00:08:39,159
Lacey.

168
00:08:39,159 --> 00:08:40,033
Yes.

169
00:08:40,990 --> 00:08:43,390
Yes, well I know she's on her way so I...

170
00:08:44,230 --> 00:08:46,623
Oh, oh here she comes right now.

171
00:08:47,550 --> 00:08:48,383
Right away.

172
00:08:49,250 --> 00:08:50,083
Right.

173
00:08:51,345 --> 00:08:54,380
- It's the end of the
day, what does he want?

174
00:08:54,380 --> 00:08:55,960
- [Mary Beth] Come on.

175
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:57,723
- I'd gotta get coffee.

176
00:09:01,680 --> 00:09:03,968
(sighing)

177
00:09:03,968 --> 00:09:07,301
I hate looking this good for these guys.

178
00:09:09,030 --> 00:09:10,040
- [Douglas] Come in, Mrs. Lacey.

179
00:09:10,040 --> 00:09:10,873
- We're here.

180
00:09:10,873 --> 00:09:12,120
Lieutenant Cagney's right behind me.

181
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:14,030
- I wanna be very clear on something.

182
00:09:14,030 --> 00:09:16,700
You're an investigator
for the District Attorney.

183
00:09:16,700 --> 00:09:18,170
You serve at his pleasure.

184
00:09:18,170 --> 00:09:20,770
Your loyalties, wherever
your emotions may take you

185
00:09:20,770 --> 00:09:22,590
belong right here, right?

186
00:09:22,590 --> 00:09:23,440
- I understand, sir.

187
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:26,500
- You're not a cop, no bleeding
blue on this assignment.

188
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:27,500
- I understand, sir.

189
00:09:30,170 --> 00:09:31,350
- What's up?

190
00:09:31,350 --> 00:09:33,950
- I'm supposed to be loyal
to the District Attorney.

191
00:09:34,990 --> 00:09:36,480
- She knows that.

192
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:38,140
Why would you think
she wouldn't know that?

193
00:09:38,140 --> 00:09:41,550
- I don't want anybody to
misunderstand anything.

194
00:09:41,550 --> 00:09:42,537
- Anyhow, the police and the DA

195
00:09:42,537 --> 00:09:44,023
are on the same side.

196
00:09:44,960 --> 00:09:45,793
Aren't they?

197
00:09:46,840 --> 00:09:48,340
- Two nights ago, a volunteer

198
00:09:48,340 --> 00:09:50,220
from the Christ is Savior soup kitchen

199
00:09:50,220 --> 00:09:52,530
discovered the body of a
young male in the dumpster

200
00:09:52,530 --> 00:09:56,210
between the church and a
building at 2141 South Vandemeer

201
00:09:56,210 --> 00:09:57,970
in the 27th precinct.

202
00:09:57,970 --> 00:09:58,803
The victim was carrying

203
00:09:58,803 --> 00:10:00,360
two different sets of identification.

204
00:10:00,360 --> 00:10:01,840
He could be a resident alien,

205
00:10:01,840 --> 00:10:03,240
a naturalized citizen,

206
00:10:03,240 --> 00:10:05,280
or an illegal with forged docs.

207
00:10:05,280 --> 00:10:07,580
He is ethnic Chinese.

208
00:10:07,580 --> 00:10:10,200
Died of a single gunshot
wound at point blank range.

209
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:13,460
Now, the coroner found this stuff

210
00:10:13,460 --> 00:10:14,570
caught in his front teeth.

211
00:10:14,570 --> 00:10:16,270
I want you to take a look at that.

212
00:10:19,792 --> 00:10:21,492
- They're little hairs, like fuzz.

213
00:10:24,070 --> 00:10:25,270
- And blue.

214
00:10:25,270 --> 00:10:26,103
- Exactly.

215
00:10:27,420 --> 00:10:30,470
The lab thinks these
are fibers from fake fur

216
00:10:30,470 --> 00:10:32,550
found on the collar of
a patrolman's jacket.

217
00:10:32,550 --> 00:10:34,050
- So what are you saying?

218
00:10:34,050 --> 00:10:36,530
If the victim was struggling
with a police officer,

219
00:10:36,530 --> 00:10:37,620
he might have used his teeth?

220
00:10:37,620 --> 00:10:39,340
- And some of the hairs stuck there?

221
00:10:39,340 --> 00:10:40,890
- [Douglas] That is the theory.

222
00:10:42,190 --> 00:10:43,850
- What's the caliber of the slug?

223
00:10:43,850 --> 00:10:45,090
- Nine millimeter.

224
00:10:45,090 --> 00:10:46,360
- [Christine] Any officer
involved shootings

225
00:10:46,360 --> 00:10:47,490
reported that night?

226
00:10:47,490 --> 00:10:48,523
- None reported.

227
00:10:49,500 --> 00:10:52,320
Now listen, Homicide is
cooperating with Internal Affairs,

228
00:10:52,320 --> 00:10:53,770
and the District Attorney's
gonna be involved

229
00:10:53,770 --> 00:10:54,963
in this investigation.

230
00:10:55,990 --> 00:10:57,310
It could be one bad cop.

231
00:10:57,310 --> 00:10:59,210
- It could be no bad cop.

232
00:10:59,210 --> 00:11:01,000
It could be a civilian in a police jacket.

233
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:03,310
- Yeah, or it could be something worse.

234
00:11:03,310 --> 00:11:05,820
Last time there was a PD
scandal, we weren't ready.

235
00:11:05,820 --> 00:11:08,530
And the former District
Attorney got creamed.

236
00:11:08,530 --> 00:11:10,390
Now whatever kind of bombshell this is,

237
00:11:10,390 --> 00:11:12,570
that will not happen this time.

238
00:11:12,570 --> 00:11:15,540
Our District Attorney
has a very bright future

239
00:11:15,540 --> 00:11:18,220
of service to the city
of New York ahead of him.

240
00:11:18,220 --> 00:11:19,640
And it's my job to see to it

241
00:11:19,640 --> 00:11:20,790
that it stays that way.

242
00:11:24,840 --> 00:11:25,960
- So?

243
00:11:25,960 --> 00:11:26,793
- So nothing.

244
00:11:28,360 --> 00:11:29,193
So.

245
00:11:30,264 --> 00:11:31,364
- What don't you like?

246
00:11:32,590 --> 00:11:35,280
- Our Mr. Trayne has already
decided what this is.

247
00:11:35,280 --> 00:11:36,490
- No he hasn't.

248
00:11:36,490 --> 00:11:37,673
- I take it back.

249
00:11:38,580 --> 00:11:40,330
- Don't start with me, Mary Beth.

250
00:11:40,330 --> 00:11:41,453
It's been a long day.

251
00:11:42,620 --> 00:11:43,453
- I know.

252
