Zero tolerance of punks,

807
00:35:44,900 --> 00:35:47,593
zero tolerance of corruption,

808
00:35:48,440 --> 00:35:50,883
zero tolerance for business as usual.

809
00:35:52,600 --> 00:35:54,667
(crowd applauding)

810
00:35:54,667 --> 00:35:55,793
Thank you.

811
00:35:55,793 --> 00:35:56,840
Thank you very much, thank you.

812
00:35:56,840 --> 00:35:59,380
- That's a good color on you, Chris.

813
00:35:59,380 --> 00:36:01,840
- Oh, thank you, that's what I thought.

814
00:36:01,840 --> 00:36:04,200
- Zero tolerance for charisma.

815
00:36:04,200 --> 00:36:05,980
- He is a good man, Tom.

816
00:36:05,980 --> 00:36:07,270
- Well he's got the Elmer Fudd vote,

817
00:36:07,270 --> 00:36:08,824
I gotta hand it to him.

818
00:36:08,824 --> 00:36:10,333
- What do you think of
the zero tolerance thing?

819
00:36:10,333 --> 00:36:11,844
- Eh.

820
00:36:11,844 --> 00:36:12,677
- [Christine] He paid big bucks for it.

821
00:36:12,677 --> 00:36:15,240
- Listen, it worked in
a bunch of other races.

822
00:36:15,240 --> 00:36:16,530
- Zero tolerance?

823
00:36:16,530 --> 00:36:17,844
The exact words?

824
00:36:17,844 --> 00:36:19,580
- [Pam] Mhmm.

825
00:36:19,580 --> 00:36:20,890
- God, with all the money
they paid for a consultant

826
00:36:20,890 --> 00:36:22,570
you'd think he'd come up with something

827
00:36:22,570 --> 00:36:23,403
a little more unique.

828
00:36:23,403 --> 00:36:24,620
- These guys don't want unique.

829
00:36:24,620 --> 00:36:26,580
They love the fact that
he plays in Peoria.

830
00:36:26,580 --> 00:36:28,560
- Anybody ever hear of
a DA who had to keep

831
00:36:28,560 --> 00:36:30,340
reminding people he was tough?

832
00:36:30,340 --> 00:36:31,710
This guy's doing it.

833
00:36:31,710 --> 00:36:32,840
- You wish.

834
00:36:32,840 --> 00:36:35,163
- He's running a classic female campaign.

835
00:36:36,150 --> 00:36:37,608
- I beg your pardon.

836
00:36:37,608 --> 00:36:39,810
- Classic, it's Christine
Whitman's campaign.

837
00:36:39,810 --> 00:36:42,620
- Huh, he should only do so well.

838
00:36:42,620 --> 00:36:44,170
- He should only look so tough.

839
00:36:45,320 --> 00:36:46,720
- I've learned the trick to getting Pam

840
00:36:46,720 --> 00:36:48,840
to spill the really good dirt.

841
00:36:48,840 --> 00:36:52,900
You gotta catch her between
drinks two and three, mhmm.

842
00:36:52,900 --> 00:36:54,050
- You don't drink, huh?

843
00:36:57,300 --> 00:36:58,890
- Not today.

844
00:36:58,890 --> 00:37:00,240
- Not the last time either.

845
00:37:02,020 --> 00:37:02,853
- Right.

846
00:37:02,853 --> 00:37:05,010
- And all I do is take you
to these margarita palaces.

847
00:37:05,010 --> 00:37:06,640
- Oh, that's all right.

848
00:37:06,640 --> 00:37:09,150
I've been on the wagon for seven years.

849
00:37:09,150 --> 00:37:12,349
I fell off a bit this summer,

850
00:37:12,349 --> 00:37:13,820
but hey I had a good time

851
00:37:13,820 --> 00:37:15,523
but apparently nobody else did.

852
00:37:19,772 --> 00:37:22,439
(Tom whistling)

853
00:37:26,470 --> 00:37:27,433
This was fun.

854
00:37:29,260 --> 00:37:30,753
I had a great time.

855
00:37:32,077 --> 00:37:32,910
Oh, god.

856
00:37:34,510 --> 00:37:35,460
I had a great time.

857
00:37:36,420 --> 00:37:38,720
I'm sorry, I'm out of practice.

858
00:37:38,720 --> 00:37:39,970
- I had a great time too.

859
00:37:42,990 --> 00:37:44,290
- Are we finished talking?

860
00:37:47,050 --> 00:37:47,883
- Not nearly.

861
00:37:49,325 --> 00:37:51,933
- Would you like to
continue this at my place?

862
00:37:53,330 --> 00:37:54,163
- I can't.

863
00:37:57,070 --> 00:37:57,903
Good night.

864
00:37:59,924 --> 00:38:00,757
- Night.

865
00:38:19,210 --> 00:38:20,403
- Zibiski, right?

866
00:38:21,430 --> 00:38:22,410
- Right.

867
00:38:22,410 --> 00:38:23,243
- He's gone.

868
00:38:26,300 --> 00:38:27,950
Someone was supposed to call you.

869
00:38:30,760 --> 00:38:31,810
They put him on the other side

870
00:38:31,810 --> 00:38:33,620
when he stabilized.

871
00:38:33,620 --> 00:38:35,090
- What?

872
00:38:35,090 --> 00:38:38,040
- [Nurse] He's stable, so they
put him in a different room.

873
00:38:39,860 --> 00:38:41,440
- He's all right?

874
00:38:41,440 --> 00:38:42,683
- Yeah, he's doing good.

875
00:38:44,850 --> 00:38:47,140
Yeah, where's Mr. Zibiski at?

876
00:38:47,140 --> 00:38:48,340
I'll get you the number.

877
00:38:49,514 --> 00:38:51,403
Mhmm, 503, thanks.

878
00:38:52,950 --> 00:38:54,563
503, that-a-way.

879
00:38:56,562 --> 00:38:59,479
(melancholy music)

880
00:40:11,483 --> 00:40:12,483
- Pardon me.

881
00:40:13,722 --> 00:40:15,305
Mr. Zibiski in 503,

882
00:40:16,590 --> 00:40:18,540
he could use a shave.

883
00:40:18,540 --> 00:40:20,143
- I'll make a note for the morning.

884
00:40:21,220 --> 00:40:22,320
- Thank you very much.

885
00:40:23,220 --> 00:40:24,589
Night.

886
00:40:24,589 --> 00:40:26,422
- You have a good one.

887
00:40:40,243 --> 00:40:42,743
(car honking)

888
00:40:54,783 --> 00:40:56,370
- So?

889
00:40:56,370 --> 00:40:58,700
- Well, they would have
been a whole lot easier

890
00:40:58,700 --> 00:41:02,120
if Angela had said the man's name was Giac

891
00:41:02,120 --> 00:41:03,700
instead of Jacques.

892
00:41:03,700 --> 00:41:05,584
- Leonard P. Di Giacomo.

893
00:41:05,584 --> 00:41:07,510
- Giac, right?

894
00:41:07,510 --> 00:41:09,439
- Oh wow, was in the two-seven, huh?

895
00:41:09,439 --> 00:41:10,272
- When I searched,

896
00:41:10,272 --> 00:41:13,310
he had enunciated more
clearly and said Giac.

897
00:41:13,310 --> 00:41:14,510
- No, that was my fault.

898
00:41:16,590 --> 00:41:18,630
- You're suspicious of her, huh?

899
00:41:18,630 --> 00:41:20,880
- I don't like that she
called in sick today.

900
00:41:22,536 --> 00:41:23,369
(buzzing)

901
00:41:23,369 --> 00:41:24,970
- Think she's gonna disappear?

902
00:41:24,970 --> 00:41:27,690
- I don't like coincidences, that's all.

903
00:41:27,690 --> 00:41:28,523
- [Angela] Yes?

904
00:41:29,450 --> 00:41:31,500
- Angela, hey, it's Mary Beth Lacey,

905
00:41:31,500 --> 00:41:32,333
can I come up?

906
00:41:35,380 --> 00:41:36,213
Angela?

907
00:41:41,410 --> 00:41:43,460
(door buzzing)

908
00:41:43,460 --> 00:41:44,683
- Good decision, Angela.

909
00:41:49,340 --> 00:41:50,173
- Hi.

910
00:41:50,173 --> 00:41:51,443
- [Angela] Hi, come on.

911
00:41:52,910 --> 00:41:55,000
- This is Lieutenant Chris Cagney.

912
00:41:55,000 --> 00:41:55,833
- Officer Lum.

913
00:42:01,360 --> 00:42:02,193
- Come in.

914
00:42:05,720 --> 00:42:07,530
- Oh, this is nice.

915
00:42:07,530 --> 00:42:09,200
- Yeah, the kitchen's huge and

916
00:42:10,250 --> 00:42:12,110
bedroom gets a lot of light.

917
00:42:12,110 --> 00:42:14,460
- What do you pay, if
you don't mind my asking?

918
00:42:16,200 --> 00:42:17,083
- 875.

919
00:42:18,300 --> 00:42:20,253
- In this location, that is nice.

920
00:42:23,960 --> 00:42:25,160
- So am I gonna lose it?

921
00:42:26,550 --> 00:42:27,760
- What?

922
00:42:27,760 --> 00:42:28,763
- My Manhattan fantasy place.

923
00:42:28,763 --> 00:42:30,920
This is the best apartment I've ever had.

924
00:42:30,920 --> 00:42:32,960
- What makes you think
you're gonna lose it?

925
00:42:32,960 --> 00:42:34,960
- She's from Internal Affairs, isn't she?

926
00:42:34,960 --> 00:42:36,368
- No.

927
00:42:36,368 --> 00:42:37,430
No, we're both with the DA.

928
00:42:37,430 --> 00:42:40,133
- But you're looking into that
homicide case, aren't you?

929
00:42:45,649 --> 00:42:48,732
(sighing) I knew it.

930
00:42:50,833 --> 00:42:52,283
I don't have anything to say.

931
00:42:56,060 --> 00:42:58,333
- Chris, could you read this for me?

932
00:42:59,200 --> 00:43:00,310
We've worked together so long,

933
00:43:00,310 --> 00:43:02,785
she reads my writing better than I do.

934
00:43:02,785 --> 00:43:04,535
Can I have a glass of water please?

935
00:43:05,520 --> 00:43:06,353
- Sure.

936
00:43:08,450 --> 00:43:10,443
- Is that a G or a six?

937
00:43:11,340 --> 00:43:12,323
- It's a six.

938
00:43:14,870 --> 00:43:15,703
- Thank you.

939
00:43:19,310 --> 00:43:20,143
Thanks.

940
00:43:24,046 --> 00:43:26,883
You wanna take a minute
and think this over?

941
00:43:28,030 --> 00:43:30,233
It's a pretty big deal, not cooperating.

942
00:44:05,600 --> 00:44:07,062
- This was at the scene.

943
00:44:07,062 --> 00:44:08,544
- [Christine] What is that?

944
00:44:08,544 --> 00:44:09,593
- Key tag.

945
00:44:13,810 --> 00:44:16,160
- Virginia is for lovers.

946
00:44:16,160 --> 00:44:18,690
- [Angela] It was on the
ground near the dumpster.

947
00:44:18,690 --> 00:44:20,263
- Why would you steal evidence?

948
00:44:21,530 --> 00:44:22,893
- I wouldn't, never.

949
00:44:38,720 --> 00:44:39,553
These are mine.

950
00:44:46,211 --> 00:44:48,320
- It's the same tag.

951
00:44:48,320 --> 00:44:51,880
- I just assumed that it was mine.

952
00:44:51,880 --> 00:44:54,660
I tucked it into my blouse
pocket, kept working.

953
00:44:54,660 --> 00:44:56,753
I didn't even register what I was doing.

954
00:44:57,616 --> 00:44:59,290
And when I got home and used my keys,

955
00:44:59,290 --> 00:45:01,330
I saw I hadn't lost my tag.

956
00:45:01,330 --> 00:45:02,453
- So you turn it in.

957
00:45:05,030 --> 00:45:06,380
Angela, what's the problem?

958
00:45:11,460 --> 00:45:13,980
- I thought I knew whose it was.

959
00:45:13,980 --> 00:45:16,480
I mean they must have made
a million of these but,

960
00:45:17,870 --> 00:45:19,130
I wanted to check.

961
00:45:19,130 --> 00:45:20,233
- Leonard Di Giacomo?

962
00:45:21,180 --> 00:45:22,013
Is it his?

963
00:45:29,500 --> 00:45:30,333
- I think so.

964
00:45:33,220 --> 00:45:34,903
I can't get Giac to call me.

965
00:45:39,433 --> 00:45:42,232
(knocking)

966
00:45:42,232 --> 00:45:47,232
(birds chirping)
(dog barking in distance)

967
00:45:49,656 --> 00:45:52,330
(kids chattering in distance)

968
00:45:52,330 --> 00:45:54,747
- [Mary Beth] Mr. Di Giacomo?

969
00:46:26,368 --> 00:46:28,618
(knocking)

970
00:46:33,380 --> 00:46:35,047
- [Woman] Who is it?

971
00:46:35,990 --> 00:46:37,133
- Christine Cagney.

972
00:46:39,350 --> 00:46:40,183
Hi.

973
00:46:40,183 --> 00:46:41,200
- Do I know you?

974
00:46:41,200 --> 00:46:42,033
- [Christine] No, ma'am.

975
00:46:42,033 --> 00:46:43,640
I'm looking for one of your neighbors.

976
00:46:43,640 --> 00:46:45,210
Have you seen Giac lately?

977
00:46:45,210 --> 00:46:47,040
- Across the street?

978
00:46:47,040 --> 00:46:48,820
- [Christine] Yes, Ma'am.

979
00:46:48,820 --> 00:46:50,560
- This is ridiculous.

980
00:46:50,560 --> 00:46:51,610
Come inside.

981
00:46:51,610 --> 00:46:55,443
- Oh, thank you.

982
00:46:55,443 --> 00:46:56,660
Thank you.

983
00:46:56,660 --> 00:46:59,540
None of us have seen Giac for over a week.

984
00:46:59,540 --> 00:47:01,540
Does he always leave his porch light on?

985
00:47:02,440 --> 00:47:03,720
- [Mary Beth] Nobody on
this side of the street

986
00:47:03,720 --> 00:47:04,700
has seen him in days

987
00:47:04,700 --> 00:47:07,210
and it's impossible to see in the house.

988
00:47:07,210 --> 00:47:08,647
- Let me tell you a story about Giac

989
00:47:08,647 --> 00:47:11,060
and you tell me if it matters.

990
00:47:11,060 --> 00:47:13,110
He barely squeaks through the Academy.

991
00:47:13,110 --> 00:47:14,320
His career is marginal,

992
00:47:14,320 --> 00:47:16,790
he has problems with every
Sergeant that he works with,

993
00:47:16,790 --> 00:47:18,330
but he takes the detective exam

994
00:47:18,330 --> 00:47:21,160
and he scores through the roof.

995
00:47:21,160 --> 00:47:22,270
Now they throw out the results

996
00:47:22,270 --> 00:47:24,250
but they let him take the test again.

997
00:47:24,250 --> 00:47:25,083
- And?

998
00:47:25,083 --> 00:47:26,423
- He decides not to take it.

999
00:47:27,810 --> 00:47:29,610
- You think he sounds like a cheat.

1000
00:47:29,610 --> 00:47:30,560
- [Christine] Yeah.

1001
00:47:30,560 --> 00:47:31,393
- So do I.

1002
00:47:34,980 --> 00:47:37,116
- Okay, I wonder if I should stay-

1003
00:47:37,116 --> 00:47:37,949
(knocking)

1004
00:47:37,949 --> 00:47:39,200
God!

1005
00:47:39,200 --> 00:47:40,033
What?

1006
00:47:42,466 --> 00:47:45,080
- The boat is gone, I
thought I'd tell you.

1007
00:47:45,080 --> 00:47:45,930
- What boat?

1008
00:47:45,930 --> 00:47:48,160
- Your friend, kept the big ugly boat

1009
00:47:48,160 --> 00:47:49,773
all winter in the drive.

1010
00:47:51,910 --> 00:47:53,043
- [Mary Beth] Thank you.

1011
00:47:54,210 --> 00:47:55,260
- [Christine] Really.

1012
00:47:56,890 --> 00:47:58,664
- The heck was that?

1013
00:47:58,664 --> 00:48:00,426
(knocking)

1014
00:48:00,426 --> 00:48:01,259
- Giac?

1015
00:48:05,870 --> 00:48:06,703
After you.

1016
00:48:09,990 --> 00:48:11,410
- Don't worry about it Mary Beth,

1017
00:48:11,410 --> 00:48:13,570
it's practically a desk job.

1018
00:48:13,570 --> 00:48:15,370
- Practically is the operative word.

1019
00:48:18,900 --> 00:48:20,090
- Oh, gee.

1020
00:48:20,090 --> 00:48:21,003
- [Christine] Careful.

1021
00:48:30,850 --> 00:48:32,450
- What they got beds down there?

1022
00:48:33,380 --> 00:48:34,213
- Below.

1023
00:48:35,090 --> 00:48:36,213
They call it below.

1024
00:48:40,668 --> 00:48:41,501
Giac?

1025
00:48:42,915 --> 00:48:45,800
(knocking)

1026
00:48:45,800 --> 00:48:46,713
- Easy.

1027
00:48:53,573 --> 00:48:56,073
(light music)

1028
00:49:04,739 --> 00:49:06,156
Well, in a guess,

1029
00:49:07,719 --> 00:49:09,886
I'd say it's a party boat.

1030
00:49:11,790 --> 00:49:13,123
- You hear that?

1031
00:49:14,830 --> 00:49:18,413
- Yeah, it's the boat
knocking on the pier.

1032
00:49:19,800 --> 00:49:21,200
- It's not on the pier side.

1033
00:49:25,490 --> 00:49:27,040
- Well it's probably, you know,

1034
00:49:29,220 --> 00:49:32,811
a lobster pot or what do you call it?

1035
00:49:32,811 --> 00:49:33,965
(tense music)

1036
00:49:33,965 --> 00:49:35,359
A crab trap.

1037
00:49:35,359 --> 00:49:37,526
- Thank you, Captain Nemo.

1038
00:49:38,527 --> 00:49:39,777
- Funny, Chris.

1039
00:49:45,688 --> 00:49:48,355
(ominous music)

1040
00:49:59,649 --> 00:50:00,899
(radio chatter)

1041
00:50:00,899 --> 00:50:03,066
(zipping)

1042
00:50:07,937 --> 00:50:11,687
- [Detective] Did you
see Di Giacomo's hands?

1043
00:50:12,920 --> 00:50:14,770
- What, he was wrapped in a tarp.

1044
00:50:14,770 --> 00:50:16,283
- Somebody cut off his hands.

1045
00:50:20,290 --> 00:50:21,520
- They cut off his hands?

1046
00:50:21,520 --> 00:50:22,353
- Yeah.

1047
00:50:23,320 --> 00:50:24,740
I gotta go.

1048
00:50:24,740 --> 00:50:25,737
There's the CO.

1049
00:50:29,310 --> 00:50:30,610
- That's Captain Cardenas.

1050
00:50:33,270 --> 00:50:34,440
- Let's go.

1051
00:50:34,440 --> 00:50:35,753
- No, she's made me.

1052
00:50:38,801 --> 00:50:42,390
- Detective Tsu, what have you got here?

1053
00:50:42,390 --> 00:50:43,223
- Swell.

1054
00:50:46,960 --> 00:50:49,360
- Busted by Captain Cardenas.

1055
00:50:49,360 --> 00:50:52,320
She looks like the type
that'll hold a grudge.

1056
00:50:52,320 --> 00:50:53,470
- Not funny, Christine.

1057
00:50:55,290 --> 00:50:58,040
- You cut off hands if someone's
stealing from you, right?

1058
00:50:58,040 --> 00:50:59,180
- Right.

1059
00:50:59,180 --> 00:51:01,263
So what was Giac stealing?

1060
00:51:02,463 --> 00:51:04,990
Chris, I don't like not seeing your face

1061
00:51:04,990 --> 00:51:06,330
when we talk.

1062
00:51:06,330 --> 00:51:07,770
And do we have to have separate offices?

1063
00:51:07,770 --> 00:51:09,830
I feel ridiculous in that room!

1064
00:51:09,830 --> 00:51:12,460
- You feel ridiculous 'cause
you were spying on your own

1065
00:51:12,460 --> 00:51:14,357
and you got caught.

1066
00:51:14,357 --> 00:51:15,440
Am I right?

1067
00:51:15,440 --> 00:51:16,273
- Possibly.

1068
00:51:18,437 --> 00:51:20,190
- [Announcer] Mr. Sharp
to admitting office.

1069
00:51:20,190 --> 00:51:22,013
Mr. Sharp to admitting office.

1070
00:51:32,437 --> 00:51:35,350
(Martin gasping)

1071
00:51:35,350 --> 00:51:36,183
- What's wrong?

1072
00:51:37,090 --> 00:51:39,618
- [Mary Beth] I'm sorry,
I thought you were asleep.

1073
00:51:39,618 --> 00:51:40,693
- Is that wrong?

1074
00:51:41,650 --> 00:51:42,483
- No, no.

1075
00:51:45,341 --> 00:51:46,334
How you feeling?

